<br>
During a fight with the Dain, I did significant damage to him, I kept the warrior in our group alive when the cleric went link-dead (fully healed him twice), I invul-tanked the Dain for the full duration of DA, and also tanked him a few rounds (~6k damage worth), kept myself alive without help using both LoH and heals.  Didn't die the whole fight.<br>
<br>
That was one fight where all the pieces fell together for me.  In that fight, I was a lot more useful than all but one of the warriors present IMO.<br>
<br>
I think Paladins as a class should be much more welcome vs. the new uber mobs that are 80k or more hp.  We keep groups going - its not completely tangible or evident, but it is obvious that the paladin provides decent tanking with needed healing, making groups last.  And in the longer fights, those things are needed and appreciated.</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#666666><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udastran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dastran</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>4/24/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>1:17:41 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: IMO it's true paladins are a lot more useful...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">hmm several things<br>
<br>
Draco, Trak are undead by VI's story line, but they are not considered undead in the game mechanics... i've hit Holyforge for the heck of it during both fights, and nothing happened...<br>
Sanctification will not help against DT's, and is ineffective against CT's AE, both slow and the knock back &lt;= was playing around<br>
<br>
As a paladin, one of our gifts is our survivability, often, I've lived through fights or live the longest in fights that turn ugly on the raid. Along with the survivability, we are also gifted with rez(revive), and under dire straits, like your clerics have died and you barely won the fight, your raid is not totally screwed since you can rez one back.<br>
<br>
In smaller groups, our ability to root and stun shines even more, we might not deal as much damage, but sure as hell nothing's gonna gate or run on us if we can help it.<br>
<br>
A lot of the preconception that paladin suck were formed before some recent changes, like Div Str, Celestial Cleansing, and increases defense cap. Definately we can't fill the shoes of 75% warrior 25% cleric... but we have our own little niche to fulfil.<br>
<br>
Dastran Elay<br>
Crusader of Tunare<br>
